HTML encoding issue with em dash in Work Edit page

comments.body: Closed with https://github.com/pulibrary/pdc_describe/pull/1086
Opened a ticket with Globus Support: https://support.globus.org/hc/en-us/requests/368239

Running the self-diagnostic tool `sudo globus-connect-server self-diagnostic` as suggested by the Globus support shows several errors related to a library needed by Python: `libffi.so`:

```
== diagnostic: systemctl status gcs_manager --no-pager --lines 10 ==
● gcs_manager.service - GCS Manager WSGI Service
     Loaded: loaded (/lib/systemd/system/gcs_manager.service; enabled; vendor preset: enabled)
     Active: failed (Result: exit-code) since Mon 2023-04-24 17:31:50 UTC; 2min 1s ago
TriggeredBy: ● gcs_manager.socket
    Process: 1464 ExecStart=/opt/globus/bin/gunicorn --workers 4 --preload api_app -t 120 (code=exited, status=1/FAILURE)
   Main PID: 1464 (code=exited, status=1/FAILURE)

Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 gunicorn[1464]:     import ctypes
Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 gunicorn[1464]:   File "/opt/globus-python/lib/python3.9/ctypes/__init__.py", line 8, in <module>
Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 gunicorn[1464]:     from _ctypes import Union, Structure, Array
Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 gunicorn[1464]: ImportError: libffi.so.6: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory
Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 systemd[1]: gcs_manager.service: Main process exited, code=exited, status=1/FAILURE
Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 systemd[1]: gcs_manager.service: Failed with result 'exit-code'.
Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 systemd[1]: Failed to start GCS Manager WSGI Service.
Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 systemd[1]: gcs_manager.service: Start request repeated too quickly.
Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 systemd[1]: gcs_manager.service: Failed with result 'exit-code'.
Apr 24 17:31:50 prds-dataspace-dtn1 systemd[1]: Failed to start GCS Manager WSGI Service.
```

This question in StackOverflow seems to be relevant to us: https://stackoverflow.com/a/62039175/446681

The fix for this should come from upstream Globus. I'd caution against hacking the perl implementation on the node(s). [Fix for this issue](https://support.globus.org/hc/en-us/requests/368239) came from Globus Support but I continue to see odd behavior from Globus itself.
